header.gameNote: OUTRIGGER RAINBOW CLASSIC AT HONOLULU HI

article.headline: Nebraska 73, Wyoming 58
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Aleks Maric scored 22 points to lead Nebraska to a 73-58 win over Wyoming in the first round of the Rainbow Classic Wednesday night. Jay-R Strowbridge had a career-high 14 points for Nebraska (7-2) and Charles Richardson added 13. Brandon Ewing led Wyoming (8-3) with 17 points and Eric Platt added 13. Nebraska led by as many as 12 with 6:24 remaining in the first. But Wyoming closed out the half on a 12-4 run to narrow the Husker lead to 30-26 at the break. Wyoming pulled to within two early in the second half and then Nebraska used a four minute, 11-3 run to open up a 52-38 lead with 10:41 to go. The Cowboys would get no closer than eight the rest of the way. Nebraska held Wyoming, who had been averaging 79 points per game, to a season-low 58 points. Nebraska will face Hawaii in the semifinals on Friday night. Wyoming plays San Francisco.
